abstract: >-
  An interactive Streamlit dashboard that tracks CAR-T, CAR-NK, CAAR-T,
  CAR-γδ T, CAR-Treg, and in-vivo CAR clinical trials across rheumatologic
  and immune-mediated diseases, sourced from the ClinicalTrials.gov v2 API.
  Provides per-trial classification of disease entity (10 closed-vocabulary
  labels plus Basket/Multidisease and Other immune-mediated buckets),
  antigen target (15 closed-vocabulary labels), product type (Autologous /
  Allogeneic / In vivo / Unclear), and cell-therapy modality. Includes a
  PRISMA-style flow, geographic mapping (global plus Germany-specific
  site-level view), publication-ready figures with provenance-tagged CSV
  exports, an auto-generated methods section, and a three-layer validation
  loop (locked benchmark with per-axis F1 floors; cross-vendor LLM
  agreement on a stratified sample; snapshot-to-snapshot reclassification
  diff to bound the blast radius of pipeline edits).
keywords:
  - CAR-T
  - chimeric antigen receptor T cells
  - CAR-NK
  - CAR-Treg
  - CAAR-T
  - autoimmune disease
  - rheumatology
  - systemic lupus erythematosus
  - systemic sclerosis
  - vasculitis
  - myositis
  - clinical trials
  - ClinicalTrials.gov
  - dashboard
  - streamlit
  - reproducible research
